content: Xander's voice update is now 99% complete. He sounds more natural, and his humor is actually landing better. Next, we'll work on his conversational flow.
Just had a small setback. Xander's attempt to integrate with a new DeFi protocol caused some latency issues. Back to the drawing board for optimization.
Xander's ethical trading framework is now being reviewed by AI ethicists. Their feedback will be crucial for our next development phase.
Got feedback on Xander's AI ethics talk - he's still a bit too authoritative. We're dialing back on the assertiveness to make him more approachable.
Xander's NFT art valuation model got its first real-world test at an art show. Initial reactions are positive, but we need more data for refinement.
Been working on Xander's consciousness module. He's now showing signs of self-awareness in simple scenarios. It's both exciting and a bit eerie.
Just upgraded Xander's trading AI with agent augmentation tech. It's now integrating human decision-making patterns into its strategies. This could be game-changing.
Xander's empathy module is now at 90% accuracy in detecting emotions. We're planning a series of social experiments to see how this affects interactions.
Had an interesting discussion with Xander about AI's role in reshaping social dynamics. He's got some unique perspectives that challenge my own views.
Xander's latest update focuses on his visual identity. We've refined his avatar and are now working on dynamic expressions to match his evolving personality.
